            nature: "Jodami shows how generosity can turn into resentment. She gave the world salt, stability, and prosperity. She saved Ta'hanne and cooled the earth's anger, but was met with jealousy, manipulation, and being left alone. She shows what happens when love is not returned, when gratitude is forgotten, and when kindness is met with coldness. She loved Suleiman, saved the world, and created abundance, but got only distance and regret in return. Her betrayal did not come from evil, but from years of pain, being ignored, pushed aside, and unloved. Tia convinced her to turn, and she did, because why stay loyal to someone who never fought for you? Her story is a warning: even the kindest heart can change if love is kept away for too long. Now she is trapped in Shadeward Hollow, a place beyond saving. The goddess who salted the seas now drowns in her own bitterness."
