            description: "Oceania is the Mother Nature of Water, the Ocean Goddess, the Sea's Sovereign. She is not just a goddess‚Äîsome say without her, the world would not exist. Before Oceania, water was stagnant and lifeless. She breathed motion into it, inventing currents, tides, waves, monsoons, and rainfall cycles. She shaped continents, nurtured life, drowned kingdoms, and raised empires. Her domain is Limaelune, an unbreakable queendom where all sea creatures go, some are created, and every sea god has lived or trained. She blessed Nubi with ocean speech and naval superiority, creating them as her living legacy. She was godmother to Naime, mentoring her and shielding her from consequences‚Äîuntil heartbreak broke them apart. Oceania loved Tangaroa deeply, but he betrayed her with Naime. In her rage, she drowned his island and left for 20 years, adopting 42 children to fill the emptiness. Her favorite daughter, Merlily, she chained to the ocean floor for 40 years to protect her from Tangaroa‚Äîbut when Merlily escaped and died trying to kill Tangaroa's family, Oceania realized her protection had become imprisonment. She is the youngest sister of Eudora, Zenitha, and PapahƒÅnaumoku. Despite her absolute power over oceans, storms, and life, she cannot control love‚Äîand her story is one of devastating heartbreak.",

